<h1>Simple Modal</h1>

<p>
A streamlined, but flexible, dialog prompts, with a title, body and footer, the simplest form of a modal is consisted of:
<ol>
<li>The modal content itself, including its title and buttons, defined by the <i>\{{em-modal}}</i> tag
<li>A modal toggler, defined by the <i>\{{em-modal-toggler}}</i> tag which is responsible for opening/closing the modal and can be rendered as any tag (such as button or a div).
<li>An <i>optional</i> <i>\{{em-modal-toggler}}</i> within the modal to close the modal</li>
</ol>
</p>

<h3>Demo</h3>

{{#em-modal configName="bs" id="modal1"}}
    {{#em-modal-title}}
        {{#em-modal-toggler class="close"}}<span aria-hidden="true">&times;</span><span class="sr-only">Close</span>{{/em-modal-toggler}}
        <h4 class="modal-title">I'm a modal title</h4>
    {{/em-modal-title}}
    {{#em-modal-body}}
        One fine body…
    {{/em-modal-body}}
    {{#em-modal-footer}}
        {{#em-modal-toggler class="btn btn-default"}}Close{{/em-modal-toggler}}
    {{/em-modal-footer}}
{{/em-modal}}

{{#em-modal-toggler modal-id="modal1" class="btn btn-primary"}}Click me!{{/em-modal-toggler}}

